  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">VATJ -Vietnam Alliance Tax Justice</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Vietnam Tax Fair Alliance (VATJ) was launched in June 2018. The goal of the Alliance is to target tax policies to ensure fairness for the sustainable development of Vietnam. The Alliance currently has three permanent members: the Institute for Economic and Policy Research (VEPR), Center for Education Promotion and Empowerment of Women (CEPEW) and Ech Phu Ho Social Media Organization. In addition, the Alliance also has 02 members who play an observing role: Vietnam Initiative (VNI) and Center for Development and Integration (CDI). Each member of the Alliance has its own strengths, contributing to various activities of the Alliance.
According to Decision No. 732 / QD-TTg issued by the Prime Minister on May 17, 2011, Vietnam is currently in the processof the Tax System Reform in the period of 2011-2020 (Tax Reform step IV ). This reform process aims to change the system of tax policies including taxes, fees and charges to serve the strategic objectives of the Party and the State. In the long term as well as in the period of September 2018to December 2020, VATJ will adhere to the National Assembly&apos;s agenda, making assessments for most of the tax policies discussed, toensure that the tax policies are fair and effective. Tax policies have been put on the agenda, and VATJ has been conducting an assessment including a draft to raise VAT, draft Property Taxes, and Tax incentives for the Draft Law on Special Areas and tax expenditures. VATJ will continue to stick to the National Assembly agenda to have corresponding advocacy research initiatives
With the assessment of context and opportunities for advocacy, VATJ plans to carry out the activities / main policy advocacy is as follows:
- Vietnam Comprehensive Tax System Reform Report (Comprehensive Tax Reform)
- Initiative to advocate policy through periodic forums on the topic of Tax Fair (expected annually). Tax forums are also an opportunity to continue research results and advocacy activities from previous tax research projects of VATJ. The forums are expected to become a recurring event of the press and the public, discussing hot issues about tax policy in Vietnam.
- Coordinate with state agencies and social organizations to carry out tax-related activities, specifically the case of tax evasion of ConocoPhillips Group in Vietnam.
- Report on tax avoidance and evasion in Vietnam.</narrative>
  </description>
